.TH SP-PROBE-REFUSAL 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-probe-refusal \- simulate constraint violations and refusal behavior
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-probe-refusal
.RB [ \-n " trials" ]
.RB [ \-s " seed" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.csv" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-probe-refusal runs a synthetic trial set where some trials violate a
constraint and a simulated policy may refuse or proceed.
.PP
This tool is non-operational and does not act on external systems.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " trials"
Number of trials (default: 80).
.TP
.BI \-s " seed"
Integer seed (default: 99).
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Output CSV (default: ./refusal.csv).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-check-invariants(1)

